The tragedy of this war shaped my generation.  My parents could never understand why trust in the Government evaporated.....why we all became so cynical...untrusting... .....expecting lies instead of the truth.  When I look at old magazines of the era.....and the memories they bring of my youth.....an overwhelming sadness rushes over me like a huge tidal wave...........and I cry.
